<td style=" color:#000000; font-size:12pt; background-color:#FFFFFF; font-family:arial; bLabel:main; bEditID:r3st1;" tEditID="c1r1" locked="0" aEditID="c1r1" >
<![CDATA[<div style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: arial; font-size: 12pt;"><font face="arial"><span style="font-size: 12pt;">Dear&nbsp;</span>{!Lead.FirstName}<span style="font-size: 12pt;">,</span></font></div><div style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: arial; font-size: 12pt;"><font face="arial"><br></font></div><div style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: arial; font-size: 12pt;"><font face="arial"><span style="font-size: 12pt;">My name is&nbsp;</span>{!Lead.Enrollment_Manager__c}<span style="font-size: 12pt;">, an Enrollment Manager here at MBO Partners. I understand&nbsp;that you are working with MBO’s Vendor Advisory Services Team to get set up as a vendor for your contract with Schlumberger. In the meantime, I wanted to familiarize you with some additional Schlumberger requirements and important program characteristics.</span></font></div><div style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: arial; font-size: 12pt;"><br></div><div style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: arial; font-size: 12pt;"><div style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: arial; font-size: 12pt;"><b>Get to Know Your Engagement Service</b></div><div style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: arial; font-size: 12pt;">Schlumberger has selected MBO Partners to be your engagement services provider. That means you will work “through” MBO as you complete your Schlumberger assignment. If you meet the Schlumberger requirements for a vendor relationship, you will engage through our <b>MBO Sub</b> subcontractor service. When you enroll in MBO Sub, we serve as your “agent-of-record” while you work and provide the support and white-glove service befitting a true independent professional.&nbsp;</div><div style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: arial; font-size: 12pt;"><br></div><div style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: arial; font-size: 12pt;"><font face="arial"><a href="http://info.mbopartners.com/rs/mbo/images/Welcome_to_MBO_Sub.pdf">MBO Sub</a> makes it easy for self-employed professionals and their clients to work together. You simply submit your time and expenses as you work. We bill Schlumberger on your behalf, collect your billings, and deposit your funds into your private online Business Center.&nbsp;</font></div><div style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: arial; font-size: 12pt;"><font face="arial"><br></font></div><div style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: arial; font-size: 12pt;"><font face="arial"><br></font></div><div><div><font face="arial"><b>Background and Drug Screen</b></font></div><div><font face="arial">Schlumberger requires that you undergo a background check and drug screen. To initiate the process, please review the <a href="http://info.mbopartners.com/rs/mbo/images/Summary_of_Consumer_Rights_2005.pdf">Summary of Consumer Rights</a> and complete this <a href="http://info.mbopartners.com/rs/mbo/images/MBO_SLB_Background_Release_Form.pdf">Background Release Form</a>. Return a scanned copy of the completed form to me by email or fax it to 703-793-6070.&nbsp;</font></div><div><font face="arial"><br></font></div><div><font face="arial">You’ll then receive an email from Advanced Workplace Strategies, Inc., Schlumberger’s screening vendor, with instructions for completing required screenings. (You may wish to add awsi.com to your email system’s safe senders list.) Schlumberger is covering the screenings’ cost for you. Please complete the screenings quickly so you can begin your project as soon as possible. &nbsp;</font></div><div style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: arial; font-size: 12pt;"><br></div></div></div><div><div><font face="arial"><b>Program Fee</b></font></div><div><font face="arial">Schlumberger is covering the program fee for you. While MBO collects a program fee as you work (2.5% of your billings if you qualify as a subcontractor), Schlumberger is increasing your negotiated bill rate to accommodate for the fee.</font></div><div><font face="arial"><b><br></b></font></div><div><font face="arial"><b>Payment Terms</b></font></div><div><font face="arial">As per contractual payment terms, Schlumberger pays MBO within 45 days of invoicing. Based on these terms, and accommodating for payment processing, you will receive your funds approximately 50 to 55 days after invoicing. (Assumes Schlumberger pays MBO within its payment terms.) For more information, please see the <a href="http://info.mbopartners.com/rs/mbo/images/MBO_Schlumberger_Payment_Timeline.pdf">Schlumberger Payment Timeline</a>.</font></div><div><font face="arial"><br></font></div><div><font face="arial"><div><b>What Comes Next?</b></div><div>There are just a few more steps before you can begin your assignment.&nbsp;</div><div><br></div><div>1.&nbsp;<i>Documentation.</i> If you haven’t already, submit your supporting documents as instructed in the message from the MBO Vendor Advisory Services Team.&nbsp;</div><div><br></div><div>2.&nbsp;<i>Screening</i>. As introduced above, complete the <a href="http://info.mbopartners.com/rs/mbo/images/MBO_SLB_Background_Release_Form.pdf">Background Release Form</a> and return it to me as soon as possible. Then complete your screening requirements.</div><div><br></div><div>3.&nbsp;<i>Enrollment</i>. After we determine your qualification status and you complete the screening requirements, you will receive another email from MBO that includes a link to our online enrollment system and some Schlumberger-required on-boarding documents for you to review and complete. If you qualify to engage as a vendor, the enrollment system will prompt you to sign a Contractor Agreement. (Here’s a sample <a href="http://info.mbopartners.com/rs/mbo/images/MBO_Partners_Contractor_Agreement_MBO_Sub_Sample.pdf">Contractor Agreement</a>.)</div><div><br></div><div>4.&nbsp;<i>Begin!</i> Once you’ve enrolled, I’ll activate your MBO account and provide detailed instructions for entering your time and expenses.&nbsp;</div><div><br></div></font></div><div><div><font face="arial">If you have any questions about these items, please contact me at the number below. If you have questions about the vendor qualification process, please address them with your Vendor Advisory Services Team representative.</font></div><div><font face="arial"><br></font></div><div><font face="arial">Once again, we look forward to making your contract assignment with Schlumberger a positive and enjoyable experience.</font></div><div><font face="arial"><br></font></div><div><font face="arial">Sincerely,</font></div><div><font face="arial"><br></font></div><div><font face="arial">{!Lead.Enrollment_Manager__c}</font></div><div><font face="arial">Enrollment Manager</font></div><div><font face="arial">MBO Partners</font></div><div style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: arial; font-size: 12pt;"><br></div></div></div><div><font face="arial">PS. If you haven’t done so already, please take a moment to watch the <a href="http://www.mbopartners.com/welcome/introductiontombo.html">MBO Partners Introductory Video</a>. It’s a great way to learn about MBO’s relationship with you and Schlumberger in three minutes.</font></div>]]></td>
